jsymbolic2.api.deprecated

Class JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated

  • java.lang.Object
    • jsymbolic2.api.deprecated.JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated

  • public class JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains methods formerly in the jsymbolic2.api.JsymbolicProcessor class. These methods can be used as an API for doing feature extraction jobs. Although these methods should still work, they do not use the newer unified FeatureExtractionJobProcessor and UserFeedbackGenerator infrastructure, and have therefore been deprecated. Also, this code is no longer maintained, so it is possible that errors might occur.

    The constructor allows the programmer to specify feature extraction settings, after which the methods of this class can be called to extract features. Extracted feature values and associated metadata are saved to files, and may also be returned in the form of a JsymbolicData object, depending on the particular method called.

    Author:
    Tristano Tenaglia and Cory McKay

        public JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated(java.lang.String feature_values_save_path,
                                    java.lang.String feature_definitions_save_path,
                                    boolean save_arff_file,
                                    boolean save_csv_file,
                                    java.util.List<java.lang.String> names_of_features_to_extract,

                                    boolean save_features_for_each_window,
                                    double analysis_window_size,
                                    double analysis_window_overlap,
                                    java.io.PrintStream status_print_stream,
                                    java.io.PrintStream error_print_stream)
                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Instantiate a JsymbolicProcessor object with manually specified feature extraction settings. Note that calling this constructor does NOT begin feature extraction from any input files; a separate method call must be made after instantiation in order to do this.
        Parameters:
        feature_values_save_path - The path of the ACE XML Feature Values file to save extracted feature values to.
        feature_definitions_save_path - The path of the ACE XML Feature Definitions file to save feature metadata about all extracted features to.
        save_arff_file - Whether or not to save extracted feature values in a Weka ARFF file. If this is set to true, the saved file will have the same save path as that specified in feature_values_save_path, but with a different file extension.
        save_csv_file - Whether or not to save extracted feature values in a CSV file. If this is set to true, the saved file will have the same save path as that specified in feature_values_save_path, but with a different file extension.
        names_of_features_to_extract - A list of feature names to extract. Note that the name of each feature must exactly match the name of the feature specified in its constructor and stored in the name field of its FeatureDefinition object.
        save_features_for_overall_pieces - Whether or not to extract features over each input file as a whole (i.e. without breaking each input file into analysis windows. Note that if this is set to true, then save_features_for_each_window must be set to false.
        save_features_for_each_window - Whether or not to break each input file into smaller analysis windows, and then extracting features from these windows individually, rather than from pieces as a whole. Note that if this is set to true, then save_features_for_overall_pieces must be set to false.
        analysis_window_size - The duration of each analysis window, in seconds. Value is irrelevant if save_features_for_each_window is set to false.
        analysis_window_overlap - The fractional (0 to 1) overlap between consecutive analysis windows. Value is irrelevant if save_features_for_each_window is set to false.
        status_print_stream - A stream to print processing status messages to as processing continues.
        error_print_stream - A stream to print error messages to as processing continues.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws an exception if a particular feature name in the names_of_features_to_extract list does not correspond to a feature implemented in jSymbolic.

      • JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated

        public JsymbolicProcessorDeprecated(java.lang.String configuration_file_path,
                                    java.io.PrintStream status_print_stream,
                                    java.io.PrintStream error_print_stream)
                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Instantiate a JsymbolicProcessor object with feature extraction settings specified in a jSymbolic configuration settings file. An invalid configuration file will result in an error being output to the provided error_print_stream and an exception being thrown. Note that calling this constructor does NOT begin feature extraction from any input files that may (or may not) be specified in the configuration settings file; a separate method call must be made after instantiation in order to do this. Also note that this constructor does not cause the paths to any input files that may be stored in the configuration settings file to be stored in the newly instantiated object.
        Parameters:
        configuration_file_path - The path to a jSymbolic configuration settings file. This configuration file must be valid, and must contain extraction settings, output paths and features to extract. It does not, however, need to specify input files (these are ignored if present).
        status_print_stream - A stream to print processing status messages to as processing continues.
        error_print_stream - A stream to print error messages to as processing continues.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws an exception if the configuration_file_path does not refer to a valid configuration file .

      • extractAndReturnSavedFeaturesFromDirectory

        public java.util.Map<java.io.File,JsymbolicData> extractAndReturnSavedFeaturesFromDirectory(java.io.File directory,
                                                                                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> errorLog)
                                                                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Obtain a JsymbolicData objects given a directory of music files from which features are to be extracted. This will also check subdirectories.
        Parameters:
        directory - The directory containing files to extract features from.
        errorLog - An error log noting any processing problems encountered.
        Returns:
        A Map with a File as a key and jSymbolicData as a value. The specific File keys can be obtained using the keySet() method of the Map object. This is recommended as then the appropriate jSymbolicData object can be obtained to get the corresponding data.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Thrown if the directory is not valid.
